tags.name: Corruption
tags.description: A form of dishonesty or criminal offense undertaken by a person or organization entrusted with a position of authority, to acquire illicit benefit or abuse power for one's private gain

tags.name: Freedom
tags.description: The ability to act or change without constraint. Something is "free" if it can change easily and is not constrained in its present state

tags.name: Integrity
tags.description: The practice of being honest and showing a consistent and uncompromising adherence to strong moral and ethical principles and values

tags.name: Health
tags.description: A state of physical, mental and social well-being in which disease and infirmity are absent

tags.name: Education
tags.description: The process of facilitating learning, or the acquisition of knowledge, skills, values, beliefs, and habits

tags.name: Public Education
tags.description: Generally primary or secondary schools mandated for or offered to all children without charge, funded in whole or in part by taxation

tags.name: Health Care
tags.description: The maintenance or improvement of health via the prevention, diagnosis, treatment, recovery, or cure of disease, illness, injury, and other physical and mental impairments in people

tags.name: Public Health
tags.description: The science and art of preventing disease, prolonging life and improving quality of life through organized efforts and informed choices of society, organizations, public and private, communities and individuals

tags.name: Sociology
tags.description: The study of society, patterns of social relationships, social interaction, and culture that surrounds everyday life

tags.name: Prejudice
tags.description: An affective feeling towards a person based on their perceived group membership

tags.name: Racism
tags.description: The belief that groups of humans possess different behavioral traits corresponding to physical appearance and can be divided based on the superiority of one race over another
